              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Soak moong dal in water for 10 mins. Meanwhile finely chop the onions, garlic and green chillies.",
          "stepImages": [
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_1.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            },
            {
              "ImageUrl": "step_2_2.jpg",
              "ImageAltText": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "stepDescription": "Remove the water from soaked moong dal and pat it dry. Heat oil in a kadai, add cumin seeds and allow it to splutter. Add moong dal, fry for 15 secs followed by onion and green chillies. Saute till onions turn brown. Add garlic and saute till the raw smell fades away. Then add chopped dill leaves and little salt, mix it well . ",
